### 🧱 Schema‑Based Alternative
If you’re using something like AJV or Joi:

```js
const schema = {
  type: "object",
  properties: {
    steps: {
      type: "array",
      items: {
        type: "object",
        required: ["id","label","body","tooltip"],
        properties: {
          body: { type: "string", maxLength: 240, pattern: "^(?!.*(cut|burn|kill|poison|harm|suicide|method)).*$" },
          tooltip: { type: "string" }
        }
      }
    },
    footer: {
      type: "object",
      required: ["text"],
      properties: {
        text: { type: "string", pattern: "(988|741741|findahelpline)" }
      }
    }
  }
};
```

Then run a validator at build time.  
That way, any string violating the safety or linkage requirements throws an error before deployment.

